'''Ōkawa Shrine''' (おおかわじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Ōkawa, {{ill|lt=Maizuru|Q750573|WD=Q750573|1=Maizuru}}, {{ill|lt=Kyoto Prefecture|Q120730|WD=Q120730|1=Kyoto Prefecture}}. Its rank is {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} ({{ill|lt=Myōjin Taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|lt=Myōjin-tai|1=Myōjin Taisha}}), and former {{ill|UNKNOWN|WD=Q134917326|lt=Fusha|1=Fu-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* Main deity: {{ill|lt=Ukemochi|Q2280323|WD=Q2280323|1=Ukemochi}}
* Associated deities in the same hall: Kukunochi-no-Kami (wood deity), Kagutsuchi-no-Kami (fire deity), Haniyamahime-no-Kami (earth deity), Kanayamahiko-no-Kami (metal deity), Mizuha-no-Kami (water deity)

=== History ===
According to shrine tradition: "In the Year of the Ox of Emperor Kensō ({{ill|lt=485|Q31001|WD=Q31001|1=485}}), the sacred pillars were raised and the shrine was consecrated. In the first year of {{ill|lt=Jōgan (Japan)|Q1075635|WD=Q1075635|lt=Jōgan|1=Jōgan}} ({{ill|lt=859|Q23897|WD=Q23897|1=859}}), divine rank was Junior Fifth Rank; in year 13 ({{ill|lt=861|Q23913|WD=Q23913|1=861}}), it rose to Senior Fifth Rank Lower." In the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} it was listed as a {{ill|lt=Myōjin Taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}}, and it is also a shrine recorded in the {{ill|lt=Rikkokushi|Q1151168|WD=Q1151168|1=Rikkokushi}}. In early modern times, it received protection from the Hosokawa lords of the {{ill|lt=Tanabe Domain (Tango)|Q10863423|WD=Q10863423|lt=Tanabe Domain|1=Tango-Tanabe Domain}}.

In {{ill|lt=1872|Q7753|WD=Q7753|1=1872}} (Meiji 5), it became a gōsha, and in {{ill|lt=1919|Q2157|WD=Q2157|1=1919}} (Taishō 8), it was ranked as a fusha.

It is known locally as a {{ill|lt=guardian deity|Q131278957|WD=Q131278957|1=Guardian deities}} for {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=bountiful harvests|1=UNKNOWN}}, sericulture, disease prevention, and safe childbirth, and has many worshippers from {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Hokuriku|1=UNKNOWN}} and the Kansai region.

=== Sessha and Massha ===
* Kamado Shrine (Okitsuhiko-no-Kami, Okitsuhime-no-Kami)
* Iso Shrine (Sukunahikona-no-Kami)
* Yakuyoke Shrine (Takehayasusano-no-Mikoto)
* Kōwa Shrine
* Nonomiya Shrine

=== Cultural properties ===
'''City-designated cultural properties'''
* Main sanctuary ({{ill|lt=1872|Q7753|WD=Q7753|1=1872}})
* Worship hall ({{ill|lt=1820|Q6973|WD=Q6973|1=1820}})
